HashMap is a class in the java collections framework that stores data in key value pairs where key is a unique identifier and value is the data associated with the key

the hashmap class is present in the util package

Syntax
HashMap<KeyType, ValueType> refName=new HashMap<>();

to add values in the hashmap the syntax is
refName.put(key,value);

to get value of the single key the syntax is
refName.get(key)

to check if the key is present in the hashmap we use
refName.containsKey(key)

to remove key from the existing hashmap
refName.remove(key)

size of the HashMap
refName.size();


